Detective.

03:24.268 --> 03:28.034
Oh, you think that was a hummer bust?
You sayin' I queered that guy's tire?

03:28.105 --> 03:32.906
I'd say res ipsa locuitor
if I thought you knew what it meant.

03:32.976 --> 03:37.106
Hey! Ipsa this,
you pissy little bitch!

05:04.466 --> 05:06.559
- Hey, guys.
- How's it going?

05:06.635 --> 05:08.569
How you doin', Detective?

05:09.638 --> 05:12.232
- Morning.
- Good morning.

05:14.776 --> 05:16.710
Detective Kelly.

05:16.778 --> 05:19.303
Hey, Sarge. Thank you.

05:21.149 --> 05:23.083
Where's Sipowicz?

05:23.151 --> 05:26.643
Hey, Lieutenant.
He's, uh, runnin' an errand.

05:26.722 --> 05:28.986
My office.

05:29.057 --> 05:33.756
I heard he flipped out in court.
You need to think about a new partner.

05:36.098 --> 05:39.033
Lieutenant, I know Sipowicz
is messin' up,

05:39.101 --> 05:41.433
but he's gonna come out of it.

05:47.743 --> 05:49.836
I realize how you feel about him, John.

05:49.912 --> 05:52.904
Both of us know where Andy is right now,

05:52.981 --> 05:55.074
and it's not runnin' an errand.

05:55.150 --> 05:57.983
He's on a bar stool at Patrick's
gettin' loaded.

05:58.053 --> 06:02.649
Andy was a great cop. Now he's a drunk
that won't help himself.

06:02.724 --> 06:05.124
I'm taking him off the street.

06:05.193 --> 06:08.959
Lieutenant, don't do that yet. Let me talk
to him. Let me see if I can shake him up.

06:31.432 --> 06:34.367
That asshole Giardella.

06:34.435 --> 06:37.962
He can wear all the thousand-dollar
suits he wants. I'm not impressed.

06:38.038 --> 06:43.738
I popped him when he was rollin' drunks
in the park, and he knows I did.

06:43.811 --> 06:47.110
You know where that wig-wearin'
scumbag hump's gonna be tonight?

06:47.181 --> 06:50.082
- The best table at Gianinni's.
- Gianinni's. You're damn right,

06:50.150 --> 06:53.813
tellin' some broad how his lawyer
made me look like a jerk.

06:53.887 --> 06:55.821
Mm.

06:55.889 --> 06:59.017
Ahh.
Leon, hurt me twice.

07:02.930 --> 07:06.798
- This is gotta stop, Andy.
- What's gotta stop?

07:06.867 --> 07:09.335
This. You're gettin' stiff
every afternoon now.

07:09.403 --> 07:11.337
Hey, look.
I don't recall...

07:11.405 --> 07:13.896
requesting any career-counselling
session from you.

07:13.974 --> 07:15.965
When was the last time
you tried goin' on the wagon?

07:16.043 --> 07:18.238
When was the last time
you tried growin' tits?

07:22.082 --> 07:24.642
All right.
Maybe we better talk in the morning.

07:24.718 --> 07:28.279
- No, no, no. Let's talk now.
- Okay.

07:30.424 --> 07:32.585
- I think we should call it quits.
- Meaning what?

07:32.659 --> 07:35.594
Meaning us being partners.

07:35.662 --> 07:37.926
Huh! Yeah, sure.

07:37.998 --> 07:40.330
Get a little bored at home,
you dump your wife.

07:40.401 --> 07:42.995
Got a few problems at work,
you dump your partner.

07:43.070 --> 07:47.564
First of all, I didn't dump her, she dumped
me, and second of all, I've been carryin' you.

07:47.641 --> 07:52.738
I know it, you know it,
every cop in the station house knows it,

07:52.813 --> 07:54.906
and I'm sick of it.

07:57.718 --> 08:01.711
All right. You wanna split up? That's
no problem. That's no problem at all.

08:03.724 --> 08:06.454
- Get your hands off me. Get your hands off of me!
- Let's go...

08:06.527 --> 08:08.791
- Let's go somewhere and get somethin' to eat.
- I can't.

08:08.862 --> 08:11.922
I'm on rug patrol tonight.
It might embarrass your career.

08:11.999 --> 08:15.025
- Andy, come here.
- Get away. Just get away from me, Kelly,

08:15.102 --> 08:17.696
or so help me,
I'll clean your clock.

08:28.482 --> 08:32.179
- Let me, uh, take care of this.
- Sure.

08:53.307 --> 08:55.707
- Hey, Ramon.
- Hey, hiya, Detective.

08:55.776 --> 08:58.939
- She just went in.
- Where'd you get that shiner?

08:59.012 --> 09:01.913
Oh, punks. They jumped me
in the basement on Tuesday.

09:01.982 --> 09:06.112
- Anybody report it?
- What am I gonna report?

09:06.186 --> 09:08.416
I just gave 'em the $46.

09:08.489 --> 09:11.515
Ramon, you don't report it,
I can't do anything about it.

09:12.893 --> 09:16.056
I'll send a sector car over.

09:16.130 --> 09:19.065
You should move back into the building
is what you should do.

09:35.782 --> 09:37.716
Hey.

09:37.784 --> 09:39.979
I brought dinner.

09:40.053 --> 09:42.681
Where's the separation forms,
Johnny?

09:43.857 --> 09:46.519
You know what? I lost 'em.

09:46.593 --> 09:49.255
- You lost them?
- I looked all over the station.

09:49.329 --> 09:53.629
- We'll both work off yours.
- We're each supposed to fill out assets and expenses, you jerk.

09:53.700 --> 09:56.464
I lost the form, Laurie.
You want me to hang myself?

09:59.039 --> 10:01.507
So am I dismissed?

10:01.575 --> 10:03.509
Do I get pizza?

10:17.558 --> 10:20.220
Ramon got mugged
in the laundry room?

10:20.294 --> 10:23.855
- Last Tuesday.
- When was I gonna hear about it?

10:23.931 --> 10:27.662
I just found out about it yesterday, John.
He was embarrassed to let anyone know.

10:27.734 --> 10:29.861
Don't go down there nighttime anymore,
all right?

10:29.937 --> 10:32.235
I've been going to the Laundromat.

10:32.306 --> 10:34.774
How's work?
You gonna let 'em put up that building?

10:34.841 --> 10:38.174
We're still negotiating the variance.

10:38.245 --> 10:40.770
Thank you.

10:40.847 --> 10:43.441
How's your work, John?

10:43.517 --> 10:45.610
I'd ask if I wanted to know.

10:45.686 --> 10:49.053
You know... we are splittin' up.

10:49.122 --> 10:52.683
You do not have to hate
the job anymore, okay?

10:52.759 --> 10:55.728
Just 'cause we're splitting doesn't mean
I'm going to stop worrying about you...

10:55.796 --> 10:58.594
or caring what happens to you.

10:58.665 --> 11:00.599
Good.

11:04.471 --> 11:06.405
Hey, come here.

11:08.508 --> 11:11.238
- You sure we're doing the right thing?
- I'm sure.

11:11.311 --> 11:16.578
Hmm? Because a lot of people stay together
behind less than what we got goin', Laurie.

11:16.650 --> 11:18.584
That's not good enough.

11:18.652 --> 11:21.746
Look, I don't want to have this
conversation every time you get horny.

11:21.822 --> 11:24.086
It's not going to work out for us.

11:24.157 --> 11:26.887
My mistake.

11:26.960 --> 11:31.329
- I think it would be easier on us if we made a clean break.
- Okay.

11:31.398 --> 11:34.765
I mean, I still have feelings for you,
and I know you still have feelings for me.

11:34.835 --> 11:38.828
- That's right.
- So I think it would be easier if we just left each other alone.

11:52.819 --> 11:55.083
A lot of good this is going to do.

12:24.685 --> 12:27.381
Anything you want, Sal.

12:31.358 --> 12:33.451
You're such an easy guy to find,
Alfonse.

12:33.527 --> 12:36.621
Thursday's at Gianinni's.
You're such a creature of habit.

12:36.697 --> 12:39.996
- What are you doing here, Sipowicz?
- Am I interrupting, huh?

12:40.067 --> 12:43.298
Was Al here impressing you on how strong
he is with the Marino family?

12:43.370 --> 12:46.635
Hey, I'm with a lady. You're crossin'
a line here. Move away from me.

12:46.707 --> 12:50.074
What is that, a threat, huh?
That supposed to intimidate me?

12:50.143 --> 12:53.476
Look around you, Sipowicz. You can't
afford anything in here. Go home.

12:53.547 --> 12:55.481
- Stand up.
- Are you crazy?

12:55.549 --> 12:58.347
- Shut up! Stand up! Just shut your mouth!
- Are you nuts?

12:58.418 --> 13:01.751
All right. Mr. Wig says,
Alfonse has to go outside now."

13:01.822 --> 13:04.848
Come on. Come on.

13:04.925 --> 13:06.916
Come on. Let's go.

13:06.993 --> 13:10.053
Get off me, you son of a bitch!

13:14.768 --> 13:17.862
- Hey, Alfonse, you okay? Alfonse, you all right?
- Get back!

13:17.938 --> 13:21.066
- Get back or I'll blow your head off!
- All right, take it easy.

13:21.141 --> 13:24.338
All right. Let's see, Alfonse.
Let's see. Is this your money? Huh?

13:24.411 --> 13:27.938
Here's your money, Alfonse. Is this the
hundred you offered me in court today?

13:28.014 --> 13:30.039
Eat it! Eat it!

13:34.621 --> 13:39.615
You're a damn psycho, Sipowicz!
You need some time in the country!

13:41.762 --> 13:44.663
Here, you big ape!
You want some dessert, huh?

13:44.731 --> 13:47.291
Here, Alfonse,
have a sock for dessert!

13:47.367 --> 13:50.461
Have one of the socks
I can't afford to change!

13:50.537 --> 13:54.735
- Aah!
- What's that need, Alphonse, huh?

13:54.808 --> 13:56.969
Something to spice it up?
Maybe a dash of wig?

13:57.043 --> 13:59.307
Here, go on. How's that, huh?

13:59.379 --> 14:02.246
- You think you're better than me! Is that what you think?
- Andy! Andy!

14:02.315 --> 14:05.546
- Look at me now! Laugh now,
you dick-head! - Get over here!

14:05.619 --> 14:08.554
- You get outta here!
- Breathe deep! Breathe deep!

14:08.622 --> 14:11.921
Enjoy yourself! You just made
the worst mistake of your life!

14:11.992 --> 14:14.153
- What is the matter with you?
- Stop followin' me around, will ya?

14:14.227 --> 14:18.095
- Get outta here! Stop followin'me around.
- What's the matter with you?

14:18.165 --> 14:20.963
- Stop followin' me around!
- What's goin' on, Detective?

14:21.034 --> 14:23.832
It's over.

14:23.904 --> 14:25.963
Are you all right?

14:26.039 --> 14:28.701
Yeah, I'm all right.

14:29.976 --> 14:32.570
Make sure he gets home.
He's a cop.

14:34.381 --> 14:37.544
- Come on. You all right?
- Yeah, yeah.

14:40.921 --> 14:48.084
# Yeah #

